The problem w/ drugs is, they make addicts.  Addiction is proven to be genetic, so if someone doesn't have an addictive gene, but tries out heroine, they'e just fucked themselves and their future children, same goes w/ most addictive drugs including alcohol.  One of your parents is an alcholic or drugie, you're most likely to be an addict of some substance during your lifetime.<br>
<br>
Also people are thinking of only the driving aspect of substance abuse relating to harming other people.  You get someone that's pissed at their wife/boss whatever, they snort a line of coke, and suddenly they have the balls to get their gun out and go on a killing spree.  Or scenario #2 you've got a_junkie_01 that REALLY needs a fix, been jonesing for a week straight, has no money and can't get any legally.  What do they do for their drug money?!  <br>
A.  Whore themselves out  <br>
B.  Mug someone  <br>
C.  Rob a liquer store/bank<br>
<br>
There are so many negatives and not nearly enough positives to legalizing drugs.<br>
<br>
