My point still stands thou, as a responsible gun user, I can't just go shooting it off out in my back yard.  I am required by federal and state laws to go to a place where that activity is &quot;acceptable&quot;.  After I finish I'm required to safe the weapon by removing all ammunition.<br>
<br>
That's pretty much all I ask of drug users.  You wanna get dusted to the eyeballs on coke, or get fucked up on some whacked hallucinogenic drugs, that's fine.  But don't do it in a place where you can walk 10 feet, jump into a car, and then plow into me.  Go to a facility where you can be monitored by medical personnel and when that shit is outta your system, then you can go about your business.<br>
<br>
Marijuana I really don't mind too much, it's been fairly well established that although it's addictive, much in the same way as alcohol, it's effects aren't as debilitating as some of the major drugs.  Don't fucking tell me how you can smoke joints and still drive thou.<br>
<br>
P.S. Brack, it's been proven that for some people Marijuana is also physically addictive in much the same way alcohol is addictive to alcoholics.  It's just a small portion of the population.<br>
<br>
