Never has a single researcher ever been able to prove that Marijuana was physically addictive.  Ever.  You suffer from 0 physical effects of not consuming marijuana from one day to the next, which is in direct opposition to physical addiction in the forms of simple addictions such as nicotine.  It might be considered mentally addictive, that's still up for debate.  I consider that a stretch, having used marijuana a number of times (as has nearly every younger adult that I know of), and I've never seen anything that could be mentally addictive.<br>
<br>
I don't disagree that there should be designated spots for getting fucked up.  I see nothing wrong with that.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brack01>Brack01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/30/03 1:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Linale-<br>
