Alcohol can produce one of the worst protracted withdrawals, up there with heroin and benzos.  These withdrawal syndromes are almost inevitable after long-term use, and I just don't think marijuana can live up to that standard.  Maybe there are rare instances like you say though.<br>
<br>
I agree with you that the use of these substances should be done in a safe location, I just think that location should be your home or any residence or publically designated area.  I think medical personel is a little overboard for drugs like pot, coke, or ecstacy.  I don't think it's out of the quesiton for intravenous or hallucinogenic drug use though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=linale>Linale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/30/03 1:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You don't punish people before they've committed a crime.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
